Charles & Colvard Ltd (NASDAQ:CTHR) Sees Light Trading Volume with 24K Shares Changing Hands - Highlight Press

























































Highlight PressBreaking Tech News, Entertainment, Mortgages and More
Charles & Colvard Ltd (NASDAQ:CTHR) Sees Light Trading Volume with 24K Shares Changing Hands
July 17, 2017 By Clarence Martin Tweet        Advertisement





Trading was light with 24K shares changing hands on Friday.  Volume was down 12.82% under the stocks average daily volume. 
 Short traders are feeling a little more bearish recently considering the increase in short interest.  The stock experienced a rise in short interest of 161.74% between June 15, 2017 and May 31, 2017.  Short interest grew 48,439 over that timeframe.  The days to cover increased to 2.0 and the percentage of shorted shares is 0.00% as of May 31. 
 Here is the rundown on market activity for Charles & Colvard Ltd (NASDAQ:CTHR).   Director Ollin B. Sykes purchased 51,498 shares at an average price of $0.93 on Tue the 6th. That brings Sykes’s holdings to $15,899 as reported to the SEC. Director Neal I. Goldman acquired 50,000 shares at a price of $0.96 on Mon the 5th. The Director now owns $256,711 of the stock as recorded in a recent Form 4 SEC filing.
 Ollin B. Sykes, Director purchased $73,422 worth of shares at an average price of $0.94 on June 2nd. That brings the Director’s holdings to $5,260 per an SEC filing yesterday.
 Here are a few additional firms who have increased or decreased their stake in (CTHR).   As of the end of the quarter Orca Investment Management, LLC had sold 3,015 shares trimming its stake by 2.2%. The value of the investment in CTHR decreased from $132,000 to $124,000 a change of $8,000 quarter over quarter. Goldman Sachs Group Inc divested its ownership by shedding 76 shares a decrease of 0.5% as of 03/31/2017. Goldman Sachs Group Inc now holds 14,547 shares with a value of $14,000. The value of the position overall is down by 12.5%.





 Dimensional Fund Advisors Lp reduced its investment by selling 69,000 shares a decrease of 24.4% from 12/31/2016 to 03/31/2017. Dimensional Fund Advisors Lp owns 214,050 shares worth $205,000. The total value of its holdings decreased 34.1%. As of quarter end Renaissance Technologies LLC had disposed of  a total of 44,200 shares trimming its position 20.5%. The value of the company’s investment in Charles & Colvard Ltd went from $237,000 to $164,000 a change of 30.8% quarter to quarter.
  On May 14 analysts at Craig-Hallum started coverage with an initial rating of “Buy” and establishing a price target of $4.00.
 The company is trading up since yesterday’s close of $0.85.  Shares last traded at $0.860 a tad below $0.91, the 50 day moving average and which is marginally lower than the 200 day moving average of $0.98.  The 50 day moving average went down by -4.72% and the 200 day average moved down $-0.11. 
 Charles & Colvard, Ltd., launched on June 28, 1995, manufactures, markets and distributes Charles & Colvard Created Moissanite jewels (moissanite) and finished jewelry featuring moissanite. The Business’s segments are Wholesale, Moissanite.com and Charles & Colvard Direct. The Company sells loose moissanite jewels and finished jewelry at wholesale to distributors, manufacturers and retailers, and at retail to end consumers through its operating subsidiaries. The Company manages its business primarily through its three distribution channels that it uses to sell its product lines, loose jewels and finished jewelry, which included Charles and Colvard Direct, LLC..






